title: Why Australia's Housing Boom Outpaced Incomes
text: 2024, Guardian Australia asked big question: “Australia’s housing market get bad?” decades, Australian home prices climbed far faster wages. short analysis uses housepack data tools examine real disposable income, detached house prices, capital gains evolved since 1985. goal visualise long-term divergence discuss implies affordability.

title: Why Australia's Housing Boom Outpaced Incomes
text: start comparing household income detached-house prices base-100 index (1990 = 100).  chart shows series rose early-1990s recession, house prices surged far beyond incomes, especially 2000s post-2020. 2024, national house price index six times 1990 level, whereas income per capita barely quadrupled.

title: Why Australia's Housing Boom Outpaced Incomes
text: Housing appreciation also fuels capital gains owners. cgt_full dataset tracks average taxable capital gains among individuals.  Capital gains spiked mid-2000s pandemic housing surge. pattern reinforces wealth divide already owned property trying enter market.
code: ggplot(cgt_full, aes(x = Year, y = Total_gain_adj)) + geom_col(fill = "#1c4c74") + labs( title = "Capital Gains from Property Sales", y = "AUD ('000)", x = "" ) + theme_housepack

title: Why Australia's Housing Boom Outpaced Incomes
text: every state experienced boom equally. can inspect 2024 values detached_ful map housing pressure greatest.  New South Wales leads pack index near 250, far 170–190 range seen states. confirms affordability crisis geographically concentrated.
code: library(sf) library(rnaturalearth) aus_map <- rnaturalearth::ne_states(country = "australia", returnclass = "sf") |> dplyr::filter(!name %in% c("Ashmore and Cartier Islands", "Coral Sea Islands"))  latest_year <- detached_full |> filter(Year == 2024) |> select(Year, Quarter, Sydney:Canberra) |> summarise(across(Sydney:Canberra, mean, na.rm = TRUE)) |> tidyr::pivot_longer(everything(), names_to = "City", values_to = "Index") |> mutate(State = recode(City, "Sydney" = "New South Wales", "Melbourne" = "Victoria", "Brisbane" = "Queensland", "Adelaide" = "South Australia", "Perth" = "Western Australia", "Hobart" = "Tasmania", "Darwin" = "Northern Territory", "Canberra" = "Australian Capital Territory" ))  map_data <- aus_map |> left_join(latest_year, by = c("name" = "State"))  ggplot(map_data) + geom_sf(aes(fill = Index), color = "white", linewidth = 0.3) + scale_fill_viridis_c(option = "mako", na.value = "grey90") + labs(title = "Detached-house Price Index by State (2024)", fill = "Index") + theme_minimal(base_size = 12) + theme( plot.title = ggplot2::element_text(         face = "bold", hjust = 0.5, size = 12),        panel.grid = ggplot2::element_blank())

title: Why Australia's Housing Boom Outpaced Incomes
text: Real wages grown slowly compared house prices. Taxable capital gains risen sharply, reflecting windfalls property investors. Regional inequality deepened - Sydney Melbourne dominate boom. short, Australia’s housing market decoupled incomes. structural factors like credit, zoning, population growth play major roles, tax policy also amplified imbalance. rise taxable capital gains aligns decades generous investment incentives. Negative gearing allows investors offset property losses income, encouraging leveraged investment housing. Meanwhile, capital-gains tax discount (introduced 1999) halves taxable portion long-term gains, rewarding speculation owner-occupation. data shows outcome - income lagging far behind housing wealth - policies help explain housing become lucrative, unequal market.

title: Getting Started with HousePack
text: housepack toolkit - together Shiny dashboard - offers several ways explore Australia’s housing income dynamics. ideas can investigate: Track income housing diverged time: Use compare_trends() “Overview” tab see detached house prices grown much faster household income since 2000s. Spot regional affordability gaps: “State Map” tab reveals states experienced steepest price growth. Try adjusting year slider compare Sydney’s surge steadier markets like Adelaide Hobart. Explore capital gains patterns: Check realised property gains evolved alongside housing prices - hint investment activity followed housing boom. Examine data sources directly: Browse “Data Source” tab view underlying datasets (income_pc, detached_full, cgt_full) trace trend originates. Example interpretation: 2024, New South Wales reached detached-house index near 250, states remained around 170–190 - clear sign affordability pressures acute around Sydney. interactive tools make easy connect long-term trends broader questions housing policy, income growth, regional inequality.
